NAME
    HTML::Dojo - Provides the Dojo AJAX distribution files.

SYNOPSIS
        use HTML::Dojo;
        
    my $dojo = HTML::Dojo->new;
        
    my @editions = $dojo->editions();
        
    my @files = $dojo->list( \%options );
        
    my $file = $dojo->file( $filename, \%options );

DESCRIPTION
    HTML::Dojo provides the "dojo.js" and "iframe_history" files and the
    entire "src" directory from the Dojo distribution
    (<http://dojotoolkit.org>).

METHODS
  new
        $dojo->new( %options );

    This returns a HTML::Dojo object.

    Optional arguments are:

    "edition"

  editions
        $dojo->editions();

    This method returns a list of all available editions.

  list
        $dojo->list( \%options );

    Returns an array-ref of all files available.

    Optional arguments are:

    "edition"
    "directories", include directory names, default 0
    "files", include ordinary-file names, default 1

  file
        $dojo->file( $filename, \%options )

    Returns the contents of the named file.

    Optional arguments are:

    "edition"

SEE ALSO
    <http://dojotoolkit.org>, HTML::Prototype

